    "no FILES BRIEFINCONTESI Summary of Fight Against Senator Bailey Given to Elections Committee By th Associated Press Contending sufficient grounds had been presentrd to justify an investiga tion of the 1830 North Carolina elec tion attorneys for George M Prit chard of Asheville today filed with the Senate Elections Committee a brief summing up his fight to unseat Sen ator Josiah W Bailey Democrat Robert H McNeill or Washington chief of Pritchards counsel in the year old contest presented the brief which asserts Pritchard would have been elected had the vote been legally cast and fairly counted and had all voters been free from coercion He urged senatorial Inquiry The committee which has before it Pritchards original and amended peti tions charging widespread election frauds and Baileys replies to each is scheduled to meet Tuesday to consider whether the allegations warrant a sen atorial investigation Says Bailey Demurs Baileys answer to the amended peti tion filed last week by McNeill for Pritchard contended the allegations were too general and termed them a drag net description adding that Pritchard had not presented sufficient grounds for an inquiry or facts to show he would have been elected To the charges on the"
